Description: Shoulder sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; white slip; exterior: on the shoulder, painted maeander and square pattern in between concentric brown lines, below, parts of two overlapping narrow rosettes; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The sherd joins British Museum 1924,1201.1053 and possibly belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1949,0516.15, 1949,0516.16, 1888,0601.556.b and 1888,0601.556.c (the findspot for this sherd is specified as the Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi). It ought to be pointed out that Cook (1933-1934, p. 43) also places 1888,0601.556.b and 1888,0601.556.c into a separate category of miscellaneous oinochoai. The modern inscription NA123a on the interior surface is a Cambridge Museum of Classical Archaeology accession number, indicating the sherd was once part of their collection.
